.","meanings":["Scottish (Lanarkshire and Renfrewshire): variant of   Pollock  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Pollock","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from a place in Glasgow, probably a British Celtic name derived from <i>pull-</i>, <i>poll-</i> ‘pool’ + a diminutive suffix. The surname has been established in northeast Ulster since the 17th century.","German: ethnic name for someone from Poland.","Americanized form of Jewish   Polak  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Maxwell de Pollok was born in 1270, in Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, his father, Herbert Maxwell 3rd Lord of Caerlaverock, was 30 and his mother, Lady Katherine Maxwell, was 28. He had at least 1 daughter with Elizabeth Lindsay. He died in 1311, in his hometown, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1270–1311":"1270–1311","1262–1307":"1262–1307","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1291–1345":"1291–1345","1240–1298":"1240–1298","1242–Female":"1242–Surnud","1345":"1345","1311":"1311","1298":"1298","before 1262":"enne 1262","1242":"1242","22 July 1298":"22. juuli 1298","1240":"1240","1262":"1262","1270":"1270","1291":"1291","1307":"1307","Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Maybole, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Maybole, Ayrshire, Scotland","Falkirk, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Falkirk, Stirlingshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1270–1311":"1270–1311","1262–1307":"1262–1307","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1291–1345":"1291–1345","1240–1298":"1240–1298","1242–Female":"1242–Kuollut","1345":"1345","1311":"1311","1298":"1298","before 1262":"ennen vuotta 1262","1242":"1242","22 July 1298":"22. heinäkuuta 1298","1240":"1240","1262":"1262","1270":"1270","1291":"1291","1307":"1307","Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Maybole, Ayrshire, Scotland":"May